msgstr ""
"Variabel yang dimanipulasi/tentukan grup berbeda. Ini juga disebut variabel "
"independen."

msgctxt "AnovaBayesian|"
msgid ""
"In this box, the variable can be selected that should be included in all "
"models, including the null model."
msgstr ""
"Di kotak ini, variabel dapat dipilih yang harus disertakan di semua model, "
"mencakup model null."

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasures|"
msgid ""
"The repeated Measures ANOVA allows the user to analyze the differences "
"between means, when observations are dependent i.e Within subject factors. "
"It also allows combining with between subject factors."
msgstr ""
"ANOVA Pengukuran berulang mengizinkan pengguna untuk menganalisis perbedaan "
"antara rerata, ketika observasi dependen yaitu Dalam faktor subyek. Itu juga "
"mengizinkan mengombinasi antara faktor subyek."

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasures|"
msgid "Assumptions"
msgstr "Asumsi"

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasures|"
msgid "The dependent variable is normally distributed for every group."
msgstr "Variabel dependen secara normal didistribusikan untuk setiap grup."

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasures|"
msgid "The covariate and the experiment effect are independent."
msgstr "Kovariat dan ukuran eksperimen independen."

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasures|"
msgid ""
"The assumption of sphericity is met. Sphericity entails that the variances "
"of the differences between all possible pairs of the repeated measures "
"conditions are the same."
msgstr ""
"Asumsi kebulatan telah memenuhi. Kebulatan memerlukan bahwa varians dari "
"perbedaan antara semua pasangan memungkinkan dari pengukuran berulang sama."

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasures|"
msgid ""
"The within-subjects (repeated measures) variables. Here the repeated "
"measures factors of interest and the different levels that belong to each "
"factor can be labelled."
msgstr ""
"Variabel dalam-subjek (pengukuran berulang). Di sini faktor pengukuran "
"berulang dari fokus dan tingkat berbeda yang menggolongkan setiap faktor "
"dapat dilabeli."

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasures|"
msgid ""
"The separate columns in the data frame that represent the levels of the "
"repeated measure(s) factor(s). These are made based on the input on the "
"repeated measures factors box."
msgstr ""
"Kolom terpisah dalam bingkai data yang merepresentasikan tingkat dari faktor "
"pengukuran berulang. Ini dibuat berdasarkan masukan pada kotak faktor "
"pengukuran berulang."

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasures|"
msgid ""
"When the subjects have been assigned into two or more separate groups this "
"variable can be selected."
msgstr ""
"Ketika subjek telah ditugaskan menjadi dua atau lebih grup terpisah variabel "
"ini dapat dipilih."

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasures|"
msgid ""
"In this box the variables that are covariates can be selected. Covariates "
"are continuous variables that have an influence on the dependent variable "
"but are not part of the experimental manipulation."
msgstr ""
"Di kotak ini variabel yang adalah kovariat dapat dipilih. Kovariat adalah "
"variabel kontinu yang memiliki influens pada variabel dependen tetapi bukan "
"bagian dari manipulasi eksperimental."

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasures|"
msgid "Components and model terms:"
msgstr "Istilah komponen dan model:"

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasures|"
msgid ""
"All the repeated measures factors and covariates that can be included in the "
"model."
msgstr ""
"Semua faktor pengukuran berulang dan kovariat yang dapat disertakan dalam "
"model."

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasures|"
msgid ""
"The repeated measures factors and covariates that can be included in the "
"model. Can also include interaction effects."
msgstr ""
"Faktor pengukuran berulang dan kovariat yang akan disertakan dalam model. "
"Dapat juga disertakan efek interaksi."

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasures|"
msgid ""
"All the between subjects factors and covariates that can be included in the "
"model."
msgstr ""
"Semua antara faktor subjek dan kovariat yang dapat disertakan dalam model."

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasures|"
msgid ""
"The between measures factors and covariates that can be included in the "
"model. Can also include interaction effects."
msgstr ""
"Antara faktor pengukuran dan kovariat yang akan disertakan dalam model. "
"Dapat juga disertakan efek interaksi."

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasures|"
msgid ""
" By selecting this option, the univariate linear model, rather than the "
"multivariate model, will be used for follow-up tests (contrasts, post-hoc "
"tests, marginal means). Caution: multivariate models (i.e., unpooled error "
"terms) handle departures from sphericity better, since these models allow "
"the standard errors to differ for each level of the repeated measure(s) "
"factor(s)."
msgstr ""
" Dengan memilih opsi ini, model linear univariat, daripada model "
"multivariat, akan digunakan untuk uji lanjutan (kontras, uji pos-hoc, rerata "
"margin). Hati-hati: model multivariat (yaitu, istilah galat tidak terkumpul) "
"memperhatikan keberangkatan dari kebulatan lebih baik, sejak model ini "
"mengizinkan galat standar berbeda untuk setiap tingkat faktor pengukuran "
"berulang."

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasures|"
msgid ""
"Sphericity entails that the variances of the differences of the repeated "
"measures conditions are equal."
msgstr ""
"Kebulatan memerlukan bahwa varians perbedaan dari kondisi pengukuran "
"berulang sama."

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasures|"
msgid ""
"If sphericity is not met, then the test will have increased false positive "
"rate (accepting the alternative when the null is true). One approach to "
"correcting this is to reduce the degrees of freedom through sphericity "
"corrections."
msgstr ""
"Jika kebulatan tidak memenuhi, kemudian uji memiliki nilai positif salah "
"meningkat (menerima alternatif ketika null benar). Satu pendekatan untuk "
"mengoreksi ini adalah mengurangi derajat kebebasan melalui koreksi kebulatan."

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasures|"
msgid "No correction is performed."
msgstr "Tidak ada koreksi dilakukan."

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasures|"
msgid ""
"This correction varies between 1/(k − 1), where k is the number of repeated-"
"measures conditions."
msgstr ""
"Koreksi ini bervariasi antara 1/(k − 1), di mana k adalah jumlah kondisi "
"pengukuran-berulang."

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasures|"
msgid ""
"Another common method to correct the degrees of freedom is Huynh-Feldt "
"correction."
msgstr ""
"Metode umum lain untuk mengoreksi derajat kebebasan adalah koreksi Huynh-"
"Feldt."

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasures|"
msgid ""
"By selecting this option, it will be checked whether the variance of the "
"dependent variable is equal between the groups by performing Levene's test "
"of equal variances. This test is only suitable for assessing equal variance "
"for between subjects factors. For repeated measures, the sphericity test is "
"more suitable."
msgstr ""
"Dengan memilih opsi ini, itu akan diperiksa apakah varians dari variabel "
"dependen sama antara grup dengan melakukan uji Levene untuk varians sama. "
"Uji ini hanya cocok untuk mengevaluasi varians sama untuk antara faktor "
"subjek. Untuk pengukuran berulang, uji kebulatan lebih cocok."

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasures|"
msgid ""
"By selecting this option, the effect size (i.e., the magnitude of the "
"observed effect) will be displayed. The used measure for the effect size is "
"Cohen's d. The effect size will only be displayed for the post hoc type "
"Standard."
msgstr ""
"Dengan memilih opsi ini, ukuran efek (yaitu, besar dari efek terobservasi) "
"akan ditampilkan. Pengukuran terguna untuk ukuran efek adalah d Cohen. "
"Ukuran efek akan hanya ditampilkan untuk Standar jenis pos hoc."

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasures|"
msgid ""
"By selecting this option, the univariate linear model, rather than the "
"multivariate model, will be used for follow-up tests (contrasts, post-hoc "
"tests, marginal means). Caution: multivariate models (i.e., unpooled error "
"terms) handle departures from sphericity better, since these models allow "
"the standard errors to differ for each level of the repeated measure(s) "
"factor(s)."
msgstr ""
"Dengan memilih opsi ini, model linear univariat, daripada model multivariat, "
"akan digunakan untuk uji lanjutan (kontras, uji pos-hoc, rerata margin). "
"Hati-hati: model multivariat (yaitu, istilah galat tidak terkumpul) "
"memperhatikan keberangkatan dari kebulatan lebih baik, sejak model ini "
"mengizinkan galat standar berbeda untuk setiap tingkat faktor pengukuran "
"berulang."

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasures|"
msgid ""
"Instead of pairwise comparisons for all possible combination of cells in the "
"interaction, list pairwise comparisons conditional on each of the "
"interaction terms. This provides as many tables as there are terms in the "
"interaction effect."
msgstr ""
"Alih-alih perbandingan berpasangan untuk semua kombinasi memungkinkan sel di "
"interaksi, daftar kondisional perbandingan berpasangan pada setiap istilah "
"interaksi. Ini memberikan sebanyak mungkin tabel istilah di efek interaksi."

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasures|"
msgid ""
"To correct for multiple comparison testing and avoid Type I errors, "
"different methods for correcting the p-value are available (note that the "
"confidence intervals can only be adjusted using the Bonferroni method):"
msgstr ""
"Untuk mengoreksi untuk beberapa pengujian perbandingan dan mencegah galat "
"Jenis I, metode berbeda untuk mengoreksi nilai-p tersedia (dicatat bahwa "
"interval kepercayaan dapat hanya disesuaikan menggunakan metode Bonferroni):"

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasures|"
msgid ""
"This method is also called sequential Bonferroni, and considered less "
"conservative than the Bonferroni method. Selected by default."
msgstr ""
"Metode ini juga disebut Bonferroni sekuensial, dan dianggap kurang "
"konservatif dari metode Bonferroni. Dipilih secara bawaan."

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasures|"
msgid ""
"This correction is considered conservative. The risk of Type I error is "
"reduced, however the statistical power decreases as well."
msgstr ""
"Koreksi ini dianggap konservatif. Risiko dari galat Jenis I dikurangi, namun "
"daya statistikal menurun juga."

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasures|"
msgid ""
" Compare all possible pairs of group means. This correction can be used when "
"the groups of the repeated measures have an equal sample size and variance."
msgstr ""
" Bandingkan semua pasangan memungkinkan rerata grup. Koreksi ini dapat "
"digunakan ketika grup pengukuran berulang memiliki ukuran sampel dan varians "
"sama."

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasures|"
msgid ""
"Adjusting significance levels in a linear regression, to account for "
"multiple comparisons. This method is considered to be quite conservative."
msgstr ""
"Menyesuaikan tingkat signifikan di regresi linear, untuk memperhitungkan "
"beberapa perbandingan. Metode ini dianggap cukup konservatif."

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasures|"
msgid ""
"When there are multiple RM factors in the model, but only plotting a subset "
"of these factors, the mean is taken across the unused RM factors. For "
"instance, when there are two RM factors with two levels in the model, A "
"(1&2) and B (1&2), and only A is selected to be plotted, the average is "
"taken of B across its levels. This means that when the mean of A1 is "
"plotted, it is actually the average of A1B1 and A1B2). This procedure is "
"discussed by Loftus & Masson (1994). When the box is not ticked, the "
"averages are not taken, and the columns A1B1 and A1B2 are simply "
"concatenated."
msgstr ""
"Ketika ada beberapa faktor RM dalam model, tetapi hanya mendiagram "
"subrangkaian faktor ini, rerata diambil melintasi faktor RM tidak digunakan. "
"Misalnya, ketika ada dua faktor RM dengan dua tingkat dalam model, A (1&2) "
"dan B (1&2), dan hanya A dipilih untuk didiagram, rata-rata diambil B "
"melintasi tingkatnya. Ini artinya bahwa ketika rerata A1 didiagram, itu "
"sebenarnya rata-rata A1B1 dan A1B2). Prosedur ini didiskusikan oleh Loftus & "
"Masson (1994). Ketika kotak tidak dicentang, rata-rata tidak diambil, dan "
"kolom A1B1 dan A1B2 secara sederhana digabungkan."

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasures|"
msgid ""
"In order to get accurate confidence intervals and standard errors for within "
"subjects effects, the data are normalized by subtracting the appropriate "
"participantʹs mean performance from each observation, and then adding the "
"grand mean score to every observation. The variances of the resulting "
"normalized values in each condition, and thus the size of the bars, no "
"longer depend on the participant effects and are therefore a more accurate "
"representation of the experimental manipulation."
msgstr ""
"Untuk mendapatkan interval kepercayaan dan galat standar akurat untuk efek "
"dalam subjek, data dinormalisasikan dengan mengurangi kinerja rerata peserta "
"sesuai dari setiap observasi, dan kemudian menambahkan skor rerata "
"keseluruhan ke setiap observasi. Varians dari nilai dinormalisasikan "
"dihasilkan di setiap kondisi, dan dengan demikian ukuran bilah, tidak lagi "
"bergantung pada efek peserta dan oleh karena itu merupakan representasi "
"lebih akurat dari manipulasi eksperimental."

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasures|"
msgid ""
"A pooled error term assumes that the variances of the contrast scores are "
"approximately equal (i.e., sphericity assumption)."
msgstr ""
"Istilah galat terkumpul mengasumsikan bahwa varians skor kontras secara "
"perhitungan sama (yaitu, asumsi kebulatan)."

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasures|"
msgid ""
"The Friedman test is a non-parametric alternative to the Repeated-Measures "
"ANOVA when there is a complete block design. The Durbin test will "
"automatically be selected when there is an incomplete block design."
msgstr ""
"Uji Friedman adalah alternatif non-parametris untuk ANOVA Pengukuran-"
"Berulang ketika ada desain blok lengkap. Uji Durbin akan secara otomatis "
"dipilih ketika ada desain blok tidak lengkap."

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasures|"
msgid ""
"This box contains all the repeated measures and between subjects factors "
"that can be included in the analysis."
msgstr ""
"Kotak ini berisi semua pengukuran berulang dan antara faktor subjek yang "
"dapat disertakan dalam analisis."

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasures|"
msgid "The repeated measures factor(s) of interest."
msgstr "Faktor pengukuran berulang dari fokus."

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasures|"
msgid "Possible to select the between subjects factor here."
msgstr "Memungkinkan untuk memilih antara faktor subjek di sini."

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasures|"
msgid ""
"Conover's post-hoc test for pairwise comparisons, if the non-parametric test "
"indicates significance."
msgstr ""
"Uji pos-hoc Conover untuk perbandingan berpasangan, jika uji non-parametris "
"mengindikasikan signifikan."

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasuresBayesian|"
msgid ""
"The Repeated Measures ANOVA allows the user to analyze the differences "
"between means, when observations are dependent i.e Within subject factors. "
"It also allows combining with between subject factors."
msgstr ""
"ANOVA Pengukuran Berulang mengizinkan pengguna untuk menganalisis perbedaan "
"antara rerata, ketika observasi dependen yaitu Dalam faktor subyek. Itu juga "
"mengizinkan mengombinasi antara faktor subyek."

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasuresBayesian|"
msgid "Assumptions"
msgstr "Asumsi"

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasuresBayesian|"
msgid "The dependent variable is normally distributed for every group."
msgstr "Variabel dependen secara normal didistribusikan untuk setiap grup."

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasuresBayesian|"
msgid "The covariate and the experiment effect are independent."
msgstr "Kovariat dan ukuran eksperimen independen."

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasuresBayesian|"
msgid ""
"The assumption of sphericity is met. Sphericity entails that the variances "
"of the differences between all possible pairs of the repeated measures "
"conditions are the same."
msgstr ""
"Asumsi kebulatan telah memenuhi. Kebulatan memerlukan bahwa varians dari "
"perbedaan antara semua pasangan memungkinkan dari pengukuran berulang sama."

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasuresBayesian|"
msgid ""
"The within-subjects (repeated measures variable). Here the repeated measures "
"factors of interest and the different levels that belong to the factor can "
"be labelled."
msgstr ""
"Dalam-subjek (variabel pengukuran berulang). Di sini faktor pengukuran "
"berulang dari fokus dan tingkat berbeda yang menggolongkan faktor yang dapat "
"dilabeli."

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasuresBayesian|"
msgid ""
"The separate columns in the data frame that represent the levels of the "
"repeated measure(s) factor(s). These are made based on the input on the "
"repeated measures factors box."
msgstr ""
"Kolom terpisah dalam bingkai data yang merepresentasikan tingkat dari faktor "
"pengukuran berulang. Ini dibuat berdasarkan masukan pada kotak faktor "
"pengukuran berulang."

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasuresBayesian|"
msgid ""
"Select when the subjects have been assigned into two or more separate groups"
msgstr ""
"Pilih ketika subjek telah ditugaskan menjadi dua atau lebih grup terpisah"

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasuresBayesian|"
msgid ""
"In this box the variable that is the covariate can be selected. Covariates "
"are continuous variables that have an influence on the dependent variable "
"but are not part of the experimental manipulation."
msgstr ""
"Di kotak ini variabel yang adalah kovariat dapat dipilih. Kovariat adalah "
"variabel kontinu yang memiliki influens pada variabel dependen tetapi bukan "
"bagian dari manipulasi eksperimental."

msgctxt "BarPlots|"
msgid ""
"To create a bar plot, select the independent variable to be placed on the "
"horizontal axis. If there are more than one independent variable, the "
"variables can be displayed in separate plots by selecting the other variable "
"in the box Separate plots."
msgstr ""
"Untuk membuat diagram bilah, pilih variabel independen untuk ditempatkan "
"pada sumbu horizontal. Jika ada lebih dari satu variabel independen, "
"variabel dapat ditampilkan di diagram terpisah dengan memilih variabel lain "
"di kotak Diagram terpisah."

msgctxt "BarPlots|"
msgid "The independent variables included in the analysis."
msgstr "Variabel independen disertakan dalam analisis."

msgctxt "BarPlots|"
msgid ""
"Select the independent variable that should be displayed on the horizontal "
"axis of the plot."
msgstr ""
"Pilih variabel independen yang harus ditampilkan pada sumbu horizontal "
"diagram."

msgctxt "BarPlots|"
msgid ""
"By placing an independent variable in this box, different plots "
"corresponding to the different levels of the independent variable will be "
"displayed."
msgstr ""
"Dengan menempatkan variabel independen di kotak ini, beberapa diagram sesuai "
"dengan beberapa tingkat variabel independen akan ditampilkan."

msgctxt "BarPlots|"
msgid ""
"By selecting this option, error bars will be displayed in the plot. The "
"error bars can represent either confidence intervals/credible intervals or "
"standard errors."
msgstr ""
"Dengan memilih opsi ini, bilah galat akan ditampilkan di diagram. Bilah "
"galat akan merepresentasikan baik interval kepercayaan/interval kredibel "
"atau galat standar."

msgctxt "BarPlots|"
msgid ""
" This option is selected by default. With this option, the error bars will "
"represent confidence intervals of the mean of each level combination of the "
"independent variables, or the credible interval in the case of Bayesian "
"analyses. By default, the confidence/credible interval is set to 95%, but "
"this can be changed into the desired percentage."
msgstr ""
" Opsi ini dipilih secara bawaan. Dengan opsi ini, bilah galat akan "
"merepresentasikan interval kepercayaan rerata dari setiap kombinasi tingkat "
"variabel independen, atau interval kredibel di kasus analisis Bayes. Secara "
"bawaan, interval kepercayaan/kredibel diatur ke 95%, tetapi ini dapat diubah "
"menjadi persentase teringinkan."

msgctxt "BarPlots|"
msgid ""
"By selecting this option, the error bars will represent standard errors of "
"the mean of each level combination of the independent variables."
msgstr ""
"Dengan memilih opsi ini, bilah galat akan merepresentasikan galat standar "
"rerata dari setiap kombinasi tingkat variabel independen."

msgctxt "BarPlots|"
msgid "Forces the graphs to show the default x-axis at y = 0."
msgstr "Memaksakan grafik untuk menampilkan sumbu-x bawaan di y = 0."

msgctxt "AdditionalOptions|"
msgid ""
"Prior: Here it is possible to set the prior distributions for the fixed and "
"random effect sizes."
msgstr ""
"Priori: Di sini itu memungkinkan untuk mengatur distribusi priori untuk "
"ukuran efek tetap dan acak."

msgctxt "AdditionalOptions|"
msgid "Allows specifying the same prior for all the coefficients at once"
msgstr "Mengizinkan penentuan priori sama untuk semua koefisien sekaligus"

msgctxt "AdditionalOptions|"
msgid "Allows specifying the prior of each coefficient individually"
msgstr "Mengizinkan penentuan priori dari setiap koefisien secara individu"

msgctxt "AdditionalOptions|"
msgid ""
"Allows specifying the width of the fixed and random coefficient priors. Set "
"at 0.5 and 1 by default respectively. They can be changed into the desired "
"values."
msgstr ""
"Mengizinkan penentuan lebar dari priori koefisien tetap dan acak. Diatur ke "
"0.5 dan 1 secara bawaan masing-masing. Mereka dapat diubah menjadi nilai "
"teringinkan."

msgctxt "AdditionalOptions|"
msgid "Specify how the marginal likelihoods should be approximated."
msgstr "Tentukan bagaimana kemungkinan margin harus diperkirakan."

msgctxt "AdditionalOptions|"
msgid "Numerical integration is used to approximate the marginal likelihood"
msgstr "Intergrasi numerikal digunakan untuk memperkirakan kemungkinan margin"

msgctxt "AdditionalOptions|"
msgid ""
"Laplace approximation of the marginal likelihood. Works better for large "
"sample sizes and very large models."
msgstr ""
"Perkiraan Laplace dari kemungkinan margin. Bekerja lebih baik untuk ukuran "
"sampel besar dan model lebih besar."

msgctxt "AdditionalOptions|"
msgid ""
"If this option is selected, 10000 steps will be used. This option is "
"selected by default."
msgstr ""
"Jika opsi ini dipilih, 10000 langkah akan digunakan. Opsi ini dipilih secara "
"bawaan."

msgctxt "AdditionalOptions|"
msgid ""
"If this option is selected, the number of steps can be manually specified. "
"The number of steps is set to 10000 by default."
msgstr ""
"Jika opsi ini dipilih, jumlah langkah dapat secara manual ditentukan. Jumlah "
"langkah diatur ke 10000 secara bawaan."

msgctxt "AdditionalOptions|"
msgid ""
"It is possible to set the number of Markov Chain Monte Carlo samples, used "
"to approximate the posterior distribution and error %."
msgstr ""
"Itu memungkinkan untuk mengatur jumlah sampel Markov Chain Monte Carlo, "
"digunakan untuk memperkirakan distribusi posterior dan galat %."

msgctxt "AdditionalOptions|"
msgid ""
"If this option is selected, 10000 samples will be used. This option is "
"selected by default."
msgstr ""
"Jika opsi ini dipilih, 10000 sampel akan digunakan. Opsi ini dipilih secara "
"bawaan."

msgctxt "AdditionalOptions|"
msgid ""
"If this option is selected, the number of samples can be specified manually. "
"When selecting this option a sample size of 1000 is used by default."
msgstr ""
"Jika opsi ini dipilih, jumlah sampel dapat ditentukan secara manual. Ketika "
"memilih opsi ini ukuran sampel 1000 digunakan secara bawaan."

msgctxt "AdditionalOptions|"
msgid ""
"The principle of marginality states that higher-order interaction terms in a "
"model should only be included if their corresponding lower-order terms (main "
"effects and simpler interactions) are also included. When enforced, an "
"interaction between A and B cannot be added to the model without also adding "
"the main effects of A and B."
msgstr ""
"Prinsip marginalitas menyatakan bahwa istilah interaksi urutan tertinggi "
"dalam model harus hanya disertakan jika istilah urutan terendah sesuai "
"mereka (efek utama dan interaksi lebih sederhana) juga disertakan. Ketika "
"dipaksakan, interaksi antara A dan B tidak dapat ditambahkan ke model tanpa "
"juga menambahkan efek utama A dan B."

msgctxt "AdditionalOptions|"
msgid "Enforces the principle of marginality for fixed effects(User specified)"
msgstr "Memaksakan prinsip marginalitas untuk efek tetap(Pengguna tertentukan)"

msgctxt "AdditionalOptions|"
msgid ""
"Enforces the principle of marginality for random slopes (See the 'Legacy "
"results' options)"
msgstr ""
"Memaksakan prinsip marginalitas untuk kemiringan acak (Lihat opsi 'Hasil "
"lama')"

msgctxt "AdditionalOptions|"
msgid "prior distribution of the models"
msgstr "distribusi priori dari model"

msgctxt "AdditionalOptions|"
msgid "Assumes that all possible values are equally likely."
msgstr "Mengasumsi bahwa semua nilai memungkinkan yang mungkin sama."

msgctxt "AdditionalOptions|"
msgid "Default Beta(a = 1, b = 1)."
msgstr "Beta bawaan(a = 1, b = 1)."

msgctxt "AdditionalOptions|"
msgid ""
"Default lambda = 1. Equivalent to a Beta binomial with a = 1 and b = lambda "
"* p, where p is the number of predictors in the model."
msgstr ""
"lambda bawaan = 1. Setara dengan binomial Beta dengan a = 1 dan b = lambda * "
"p, di mana p adalah jumlah prediktor dalam model."

msgctxt "AdditionalOptions|"
msgid ""
"Default u = 1. Equivalent to a Beta binomial with a = 1 and b = p^u, where p "
"is the number of predictors in the model."
msgstr ""
"u bawaan = 1. Setara dengan binomial Beta dengan a = 1 dan b = p^u, di mana "
"p adalah jumlah prediktor dalam model."

msgctxt "AdditionalOptions|"
msgid "Default p = 0.5."
msgstr "p bawaan = 0.5."

msgctxt "AdditionalOptions|"
msgid ""
"Allows the user to select the prior inclusion probability for the desired "
"variable"
msgstr ""
"Mengizinkan pengguna untuk memilih probabilitas inklusi priori untuk "
"variabel teringinkan"

msgctxt "DefaultOptions|"
msgid ""
"By selecting this option, the inclusion probability of each component (i.e., "
"model term) in the models will be calculated. The inclusion probability is "
"the probability that a fixed factor is included in the model given the "
"observed data. It also calculates the BF inclusion, which are the odds of "
"obtaining the observed data under models with the predictor vs models "
"without it."
msgstr ""
"Denga memilih opsi ini, probabilitas inklusi dari setiap komponen (yaitu, "
"istilah model) dalam model akan dihitung. Probabilitas inklusi adalah "
"probabilitas yang faktor tetap disertakan dalam model diberikan data "
"terobservasi. Itu juga menghitung inklusi BF, yang mana ganjil pengambilan "
"data terobservasi di bawah model dengan prediktor vs model tanpa itu."

msgctxt "DefaultOptions|"
msgid ""
"When this option is selected, each model where the component is included "
"will be used to estimate the effect (i.e., inclusion probability) of the "
"component. When the option Effects is selected, this method is used by "
"default."
msgstr ""
"Ketika opsi ini dipilih, setiap model di mana komponen disertakan akan "
"digunakan untuk mengestimasi efek (yaitu, probabilitas inklusi) dari "
"komponen. Ketika opsi Efek dipilih, metode ini digunakan secara bawaan."

msgctxt "DefaultOptions|"
msgid ""
" When this option is selected, only models with exactly that component will "
"be included in the analysis. Therefore, interactions with the component are "
"excluded. Compares models that include the component to equivalent models "
"excluding the component."
msgstr ""
" Ketika opsi ini dipilih, hanya model dengan komponen yang tepat akan "
"disertakan dalam analisis. Oleh karena itu, interaksi dengan komponen "
"dikecualikan. Membandingkan model yang mencakup komponen ke model sama "
"mengecualikan komponen."

msgctxt "DefaultOptions|"
msgid ""
"By selecting this option, a table with the model averaged posterior summary "
"will be displayed. This table includes information about the model averaged "
"posterior mean, the standard deviation, and the credible interval for each "
"level of the fixed factors and their interactions."
msgstr ""
"Dengan memilih opsi ini, tabel dengan model ringkasan posterior dirata akan "
"ditampilkan. Tabel ini mencakup informasi tentang model rerata posterior "
"dirata, deviasi standar, dan interval kredibel untuk setiap tingkat dari "
"faktor tetap dan interaksinya."

msgctxt "DefaultOptions|"
msgid ""
"Displays a table with the mean and credible interval of the averaged R², "
"meaning the proportion of variance in the outcome variable explained by the "
"predictors, which are based on the model averaged posterior distribution."
msgstr ""
"Menampilkan tabel dengan rerata dan interval kredibel dari R² dirata, "
"artinya proporsi dari varians di variabel hasil dijelaskan oleh prediktor, "
"yang mana berdasarkan pada model distribusi posterior dirata."

msgctxt "DefaultOptions|"
msgid ""
"When this option is selected, the mean, standard deviation, and the sample "
"size will be displayed for each level combination of the independent "
"variable. Moreover, it displays the credible interval, which refers to the "
"interval in which the true value of the mean lies based on a certain "
"probability. By default this is set to 95%."
msgstr ""
"Ketika opsi ini dipilih, reratam deviasi standar, dan ukuran sampel akan "
"ditampilkan untuk setiap kombinasi tingkat variabel independen. Selain itu, "
"itu menampilkan interval kredibel, yang merujuk ke interval yang mana nilai "
"kebenaran rerata berdasarkan probabilitas tertentu. Secara bawaan ini diatur "
"ke 95%."

msgctxt "DefaultOptions|"
msgid "Compares each model against the model selected here"
msgstr "Membandingkan setiap model melawan model dipilih di sini"

msgctxt "DefaultOptions|"
msgid "All models are compared to the best model"
msgstr "Semua model dibandingkan dengan model terbaik"

msgctxt "DefaultOptions|"
msgid "All models are compared to the null model"
msgstr "Semua model dibandingkan dengan model null"

msgctxt "DefaultOptions|"
msgid "Gives the option to limit the number of models being displayed."
msgstr "Memberikan opsi untuk membatasi jumlah model sedang ditampilkan."

msgctxt "DefaultOptions|"
msgid "Select this so that there is no limit."
msgstr "Pilih ini jadi tidak ada batas."

msgctxt "DefaultOptions|"
msgid ""
"Select this to limit the number of displayed models. Set to 10 by default, "
"but this can be changed by the user."
msgstr ""
"Pilih ini untuk membatasi jumlah model tertampil. Diatur ke 10 secara "
"bawaan, tetapi ini dapat diubah oleh pengguna."

msgctxt "DefaultOptions|"
msgid ""
"By selecting this option, plots illustrating the model averaged posterior "
"distribution of each fixed factor and interaction will be displayed."
msgstr ""
"Dengan memilih opsi ini, diagram mengilustrasikan distribusi posterior "
"dirata model dari setiap faktor tetap dan interaksi akan ditampilkan."

msgctxt "DefaultOptions|"
msgid ""
"When this option is selected, one plot for each factor will be displayed. "
"Therefore, the posterior distribution of each level of the factor will be "
"shown in the same plot."
msgstr ""
"Ketika opsi ini dipilih, satu diagram untuk setiap faktor akan ditampilkan. "
"Oleh karena itu, distribusi posterior dari setiap tingkat faktor akan "
"ditunjukkan dalam diagram sama."

msgctxt "DefaultOptions|"
msgid ""
"When this option is selected, a plot for each level of the factors will be "
"displayed. Therefore, the posterior distribution of each level of the factor "
"will be shown in a different plot."
msgstr ""
"Ketika opsi ini dipilih, diagram untuk setiap tingkat faktor akan "
"ditampilkan. Oleh karena itu, distribusi posterior dari setiap tingkat "
"faktor akan ditunjukkan dalam diagram berbeda."

msgctxt "DefaultOptions|"
msgid ""
"Checks the validity of the distributional assumption of the data set. "
"Specifically, the plot shows whether the residuals are normally distributed. "
"Systematic deviations from the straight line indicate that the residuals "
"might not be normally distributed."
msgstr ""
"Memeriksa validitas asumsi distribusional rangkaian data. Secara spesifik, "
"diagram menunjukkan apakah residu didistribusikan secara normal. Deviasi "
"sistematis dari garis lurus mengindikasikan bahwa residu mungkin tidak "
"didistribusikan secara normal."

msgctxt "DefaultOptions|"
msgid ""
"By selecting this option, a plot of the posterior distribution of the R2 (i."
"e., explained variance) will be displayed."
msgstr ""
"Dengan memilih opsi ini, diagram distribusi posterior dari R2 (yaitu, "
"variabel terjelas) akan ditampilkan."

msgctxt "DescriptivesPlots|"
msgid ""
"To create a descriptive plot, select the independent variable to be placed "
"on the horizontal axis. If there is more than one independent variables, "
"they can be visualized in a single plot by placing the second variable in "
"'Separate Lines', or visualized in separate plots by placing the variable in "
"'Separate Plots'."
msgstr ""
"Untuk membuat diagram deskriptif, pilih variabel independen untuk "
"ditempatkan pada sumbu horizontal. Jika ada lebih dari satu variabel "
"independen, mereka dapat divisualisasikan dalam satu diagram dengan "
"menempatkan variabel kedua di 'Baris Terpisah', atau divisualisasikan dalam "
"diagram terpisah dengan menempatkan variabel di 'Diagram Terpisah'."

msgctxt "DescriptivesPlots|"
msgid "The independent variables included in the analysis."
msgstr "Variabel independen disertakan dalam analisis."

msgctxt "DescriptivesPlots|"
msgid ""
"Select the independent variable that should be displayed on the horizontal "
"axis of the plot."
msgstr ""
"Pilih variabel independen yang harus ditampilkan pada sumbu horizontal "
"diagram."

msgctxt "DescriptivesPlots|"
msgid ""
"By placing an independent variable in this box, different lines "
"corresponding to the different levels of the independent variable will be "
"displayed."
msgstr ""
"Dengan menempatkan variabel independen di kotak ini, beberapa baris sesuai "
"dengan beberapa tingkat variabel independen akan ditampilkan."

msgctxt "DescriptivesPlots|"
msgid ""
" By placing an independent variable in this box, different plots "
"corresponding to the different levels of the independent variable will be "
"displayed."
msgstr ""
" Dengan menempatkan variabel independen di kotak ini, beberapa diagram "
"sesuai dengan beberapa tingkat variabel independen akan ditampilkan."

msgctxt "ModelTerms|"
msgid "All the independent variables that can be included in the model."
msgstr "Semua variabel independen yang dapat disertakan dalam model."

msgctxt "PostHocTests|"
msgid "To conduct a post hoc test, drag the desired factor to the right box."
msgstr ""
"Untuk mengonduksi uji pos hoc, seret faktor teringinkan ke kotak kanan."

msgctxt "PostHocTests|"
msgid ""
"When selecting this option, the prior odds will be corrected for multiple "
"testing. This option is selected by default. At the moment, no output will "
"be generated for the post hoc test when this option is not selected."
msgstr ""
"Ketika memilih opsi ini, priori ganjil akan dikoreksikan untuk beberapa "
"pengujian. Opsi ini dipilih secara bawaan. Saat ini, tidak ada luaran akan "
"dihasilkan untuk uji pos hoc ketika opsi ini tidak dipilih."

msgctxt "SingleModelInference|"
msgid ""
"Here, a single model can be specified to obtain information about the "
"posterior of this specific model, including a table with the posterior "
"summary and plots of the marginal posterior."
msgstr ""
"Di sini, satu model dapat ditentukan untuk mengambil informasi tentang "
"posterior model tertentu ini, mencakup tabel dengan ringkasan posterior dan "
"diagram posterior margin."

msgctxt "SingleModelInference|"
msgid "This box contains all the factors included in the model."
msgstr "Kotak ini berisi semua faktor disertakan dalam model."

msgctxt "SingleModelInference|"
msgid "Select the factors that should be included in the model."
msgstr "Pilih faktor yang harus disertakan dalam model."

msgctxt "SingleModelInference|"
msgid ""
"A table with the posterior summary for the single model, specified in the "
"assignment box, will be displayed. This table provides information about the "
"single model posterior mean, the standard deviation, and the credible "
"interval for each level of the fixed factors and their interaction included "
"in the model. This is different from the estimate option in Output, since "
"the estimates option provides the posterior summary averaged over all the "
"models included in the analysis, while this option gives the posterior "
"summary for the single specified model only."
msgstr ""
"Tabel dengan ringkasan posterior untuk satu model, ditentukan dalam kotak "
"penugasan, akan ditampilkan. Tabel ini memberikan informasi tentang satu "
"model rerata posterior, deviasi standar, dan interval kredibel untuk setiap "
"tingkat dari faktor tetap dan interaksinya disertakan dalam model. Ini "
"berbeda dari opsi estimasi di Luaran, sejak opsi estimasi memberikan "
"ringkasan posterior diratakan antara seluruh model disertakan dalam "
"analisis, sementara opsi ini memberikan ringkasan posterior untuk hanya satu "
"model tertentu."

msgctxt "SingleModelInference|"
msgid ""
"Displays a table with the mean and credible interval for the model R², "
"meaning the proportion of variance in the outcome variable explained by the "
"specified predictor."
msgstr ""
"Menampilkan tabel dengan rerata dan interval kredibel untuk model R², "
"artinya proporsi varians dalam variabel hasil dijelaskan oleh prediktor "
"tertentu."

msgctxt "SingleModelInference|"
msgid ""
"By selecting this option, plots illustrating the posterior distribution of "
"each fixed factor and interaction included in the single model will be "
"generated."
msgstr ""
"Dengan memilih opsi ini, diagram mengilustrasikan distribusi posterior dari "
"setiap faktor tetap dan interaksi disertakan dalam satu model akan "
"dihasilkan."

msgctxt "SingleModelInference|"
msgid ""
"When this option is selected, one plot for each factor will be displayed. "
"Therefore, the posterior distribution of each level of the factor will be "
"shown in the same plot."
msgstr ""
"Ketika opsi ini dipilih, satu diagram untuk setiap faktor akan ditampilkan. "
"Oleh karena itu, distribusi posterior dari setiap tingkat faktor akan "
"ditunjukkan dalam diagram sama."

msgctxt "SingleModelInference|"
msgid ""
"When this option is selected, a plot for each level of the factors will be "
"displayed. Therefore, the posterior distribution of each level of the factor "
"will be shown in a different plot."
msgstr ""
"Ketika opsi ini dipilih, diagram untuk setiap tingkat faktor akan "
"ditampilkan. Oleh karena itu, distribusi posterior dari setiap tingkat "
"faktor akan ditunjukkan dalam diagram berbeda."

msgctxt "SingleModelInference|"
msgid ""
"Checks the validity of the distributional assumption of the data set. "
"Specifically, the plot shows whether the residuals are normally distributed. "
"Systematic deviations from the straight line indicate that the residuals "
"might not be normally distributed."
msgstr ""
"Memeriksa validitas asumsi distribusional rangkaian data. Secara spesifik, "
"diagram menunjukkan apakah residu didistribusikan secara normal. Deviasi "
"sistematis dari garis lurus mengindikasikan bahwa residu mungkin tidak "
"didistribusikan secara normal."

msgctxt "SingleModelInference|"
msgid ""
"By selecting this option, a plot of the posterior distribution of the R2 (i."
"e., explained variance) will be displayed."
msgstr ""
"Dengan memilih opsi ini, diagram distribusi posterior dari R2 (yaitu, "
"variabel terjelas) akan ditampilkan."

msgctxt "AssumptionChecks|"
msgid ""
"By selecting this option, it will be checked whether the variance of the "
"dependent variable is equal between the groups by performing Levene's test "
"of equal variances."
msgstr ""
"Dengan memilih opsi ini, itu akan diperiksa apakah varians dari variabel "
"independen sama antara grup dengan melakukan uji Levene dari varians sama."

msgctxt "AssumptionChecks|"
msgid ""
"If the assumption of homogeneity is not met, corrections can be selected."
msgstr "Jika asumsi homogenitas tidak terpenuhi, koreksi dapat dipilih."

msgctxt "AssumptionChecks|"
msgid "No homogeneity correction."
msgstr "Tidak ada koreksi homogenitas."

msgctxt "AssumptionChecks|"
msgid ""
" If the homogeneity assumption is not met, this correction could be used. "
"This correction is only available for one-way ANOVA."
msgstr ""
" Jika asumsi homogenitas tidak terpenuhi, koreksi ini dapat digunakan. "
"Koreksi ini hanya tersedia untuk ANOVA satu arah."

msgctxt "AssumptionChecks|"
msgid ""
"If the homogeneity assumption is not met, this correction could be used. "
"This correction is only available for one-way ANOVA."
msgstr ""
"Jika asumsi homogenitas tidak terpenuhi, koreksi ini dapat digunakan. "
"Koreksi ini hanya tersedia untuk ANOVA satu arah."

msgctxt "Contrasts|"
msgid ""
"For each independent variable, you can select a specific contrast in the "
"right column by clicking on 'none' and choosing the desired contrast."
msgstr ""
"Untuk setiap variabel independen, Anda dapat memilih kontras tertentu di "
"kolom kanan dengan mengklik 'tidak ada' dan memilih kontras teringinkan."

msgctxt "Contrasts|"
msgid ""
"By selecting this option, the univariate linear model, rather than the "
"multivariate model, will be used for follow-up tests (contrasts, post-hoc "
"tests, marginal means). Caution: multivariate models (i.e., unpooled error "
"terms) handle departures from sphericity better, since these models allow "
"the standard errors to differ for each level of the repeated measure(s) "
"factor(s)."
msgstr ""
"Dengan memilih opsi ini, model linear univariat, daripada model multivariat, "
"akan digunakan untuk uji lanjutan (kontras, uji pos-hoc, rerata margin). "
"Hati-hati: model multivariat (yaitu, istilah galat tidak terkumpul) "
"memperhatikan keberangkatan dari kebulatan lebih baik, sejak model ini "
"mengizinkan galat standar berbeda untuk setiap tingkat faktor pengukuran "
"berulang."

msgctxt "Contrasts|"
msgid ""
"By selecting this option, confidence intervals for the estimated mean "
"difference and effect size will be included. By default the confidence level "
"is set to 95%. This can be changed into the desired percentage."
msgstr ""
"Dengan memilih opsi ini, interval kepercayaan untuk perbedaan rerata "
"terestimasi dan ukuran efek akan disertakan. Secara bawaan tingkat "
"kepercayaan diatur ke 95%. Ini dapat diubah menjadi persentase teringinkan."

msgctxt "Contrasts|"
msgid "Effect size (Cohen's d)"
msgstr "Ukuran efek (d Cohen)"

msgctxt "Contrasts|"
msgid ""
"Include standardized mean differences, based on the effectsize function in "
"the emmeans package."
msgstr ""
"Sertakan perbedaan rerata terstandardisasi, berdasarkan fungsi ukuran efek "
"dalam paket emrerata."

msgctxt "DescriptivePlots|"
msgid ""
"To create a descriptive plot, select the independent variable to be placed "
"on the horizontal axis. If there are more than one independent variable, "
"they can be visualized in a single plot by placing the second variable in "
"'Separate Lines,' or visualized in separate plots by placing the variable in "
"'Separate Plots'."
msgstr ""
"Untuk membuat diagram deskriptif, pilih variabel independen untuk "
"ditempatkan pada sumbu horizontal. Jika ada lebih dari satu variabel "
"independen, mereka dapat divisualisasikan dalam satu diagram dengan "
"menempatkan variabel kedua di 'Baris Terpisah', atau divisualisasikan dalam "
"diagram terpisah dengan menempatkan variabel di 'Diagram Terpisah'."

msgctxt "DescriptivePlots|"
msgid "The independent variables included in the analysis."
msgstr "Variabel independen disertakan dalam analisis."

msgctxt "DescriptivePlots|"
msgid ""
"Select the independent variable that should be displayed on the horizontal "
"axis of the plot."
msgstr ""
"Pilih variabel independen yang harus ditampilkan pada sumbu horizontal "
"diagram."

msgctxt "DescriptivePlots|"
msgid ""
"By placing an independent variable in this box, different lines "
"corresponding to the different levels of the independent variable will be "
"displayed."
msgstr ""
"Dengan menempatkan variabel independen di kotak ini, beberapa baris sesuai "
"dengan beberapa tingkat variabel independen akan ditampilkan."

msgctxt "DescriptivePlots|"
msgid ""
"By placing an independent variable in this box, different plots "
"corresponding to the different levels of the independent variable will be "
"displayed."
msgstr ""
"Dengan menempatkan variabel independen di kotak ini, beberapa diagram sesuai "
"dengan beberapa tingkat variabel independen akan ditampilkan."

msgctxt "Display|"
msgid ""
"When this option is selected, the mean, standard deviation, and the sample "
"size will be displayed for each level combination of the independent "
"variables."
msgstr ""
"Ketika opsi ini dipilih, rerata, deviasi standar, dan ukuran sampel akan "
"ditampilkan untuk setiap kombinasi tingkat dari variabel independen."

msgctxt "Display|"
msgid ""
"By selecting this option, the specific types of calculations to estimate the "
"effect size can be specified."
msgstr ""
"Dengan memilih opsi ini, jenis tertentu dari perhitungan untuk mengestimasi "
"ukuran efek dapat ditentukan."

msgctxt "Display|"
msgid ""
"Omega squared is calculated as an estimate of the effect size. This is "
"considered a less biased estimate of the effect size, compared to η2 . "
"(Kroes & Finley, 2023)."
msgstr ""
"Omega kuadrat dihitung sebagai estimasi ukuran efek. Ini dianggap estimasi "
"tidak bias dari ukuran efek, dibandingkan dengan η2 . (Kroes & Finley, 2023)."

msgctxt "Display|"
msgid ""
"Partial Omega squared is calculated as an estimate of the effect size. "
"Partial ω2 measures the effect size of the predictor in the context of "
"multiple factors or covariates, isolating its unique contribution."
msgstr ""
"Omega kuadrat parsial dihitung sebagai estimasi ukuran efek. ω2 parsial "
"mengukur ukuran efek dari prediktor dalam konteks dari beberapa faktor atau "
"kovariat, mengisolasikan kontribusi uniknya."

msgctxt "Display|"
msgid ""
"Eta-squared is calculated as an estimate of the effect size. However, this "
"method is considered to overestimate the population variance, making it hard "
"to compare the effect of the same variable across different studies (Goss-"
"Sampson, 2018; Kroes & Finley, 2023)."
msgstr ""
"Eta-kuadrat dihitung sebagai estimasi dari ukuran efek. Namun, metode ini "
"dianggap melebihkan varians populasi, membuatnya sulit untuk membandingkan "
"efek dari variabel sama melintasi beberapa studi (Goss-Sampson, 2018; Kroes "
"& Finley, 2023)."

msgctxt "Display|"
msgid ""
"Partial eta-squared is calculated as an estimate of the effect size. Partial "
"η2 measures the effect size of the predictor in the context of multiple "
"factors or covariates, isolating its unique contribution."
msgstr ""
"Eta-kuadrat parsial dihitung sebagai estimasi ukuran efek. η2 parsial "
"mengukur ukuran efek dari prediktor dalam konteks dari beberapa faktor atau "
"kovariat, mengisolasikan kontribusi uniknya."

msgctxt "Display|"
msgid ""
"Displays confidence intervals for the effect size. Set at 95% by default but "
"can be changed into the desired percentage."
msgstr ""
"Menampilkan interval kepercayaan untuk ukuran efek. Diatur ke 95% secara "
"bawaan tetapi dapat diubah menjadi persentasi teringinkan."

msgctxt "Display|"
msgid ""
"Shows the maximum ratio of the likelihood of the obtained p value under H1 "
"vs the likelihood of the obtained p value under H0. For example, if the two-"
"sided p-value equals .05, the Vovk-Sellke MPR equals 2.46, indicating that "
"this p-value is at most 2.46 times more likely to occur under H1 than under "
"H0"
msgstr ""
"Menampilkan rasio maksimum dari kemungkinan nilai p terambil di bawah H1 vs "
"nilai p terambil di bawah H0. Contohnya, jika nilai-p dua sisi sama "
"dengan .05, MPR Vovk-Sellke sama dengan 2.46, mengindikasikan bahwa nilai-p "
"ini kemungkinan lebih banyak 2.46 kali lebih besar terjadi di bawah H1 dari "
"di bawah H0"

msgctxt "Export|"
msgid ""
"Save the residuals of the most complex model as a new column in the data "
"file."
msgstr ""
"Simpan residu dari model lebih kompleks sebagai kolom baru dalam berkas data."

msgctxt "Export|"
msgid ""
"Appends raw residuals, meaning the simple difference between observed values "
"and predicted values. Selected by default."
msgstr ""
"Menambahkan residu mentah, artinya perbedaan sederhana antara nilai "
"terobservasi dan nilai terprediksi. Dipilih secara bawaan."

msgctxt "Export|"
msgid ""
"Divides residuals by estimate of standard error of the residuals and adjusts "
"for the leverage of each data point. Use when there are assumption "
"violations as it is more robust."
msgstr ""
"Membagikan residu berdasarkan estimasi galat standar dari residu dan "
"menyesuaikan untuk perkiraan dari setiap titik data. Gunakan ketika ada "
"pelanggaran asumsi karena lebih kuat."

msgctxt "Export|"
msgid ""
"Divides residuals by estimate of the standard deviation of the residuals."
msgstr "Membagikan residu berdasarkan estimasi deviasi standar dari residu."

msgctxt "Export|"
msgid ""
"Save the predictions of the most complex model as a new column in the data "
"file."
msgstr ""
"Simpan prediksi untuk model lebih kompleks sebagai kolom baru dalam berkas "
"data."

msgctxt "MarginalMeans|"
msgid ""
"When this option is selected, the mean for each level of the independent "
"variable, adjusted for all the other variables in the model, is calculated."
msgstr ""
"Ketika opsi ini dipilih, rerata untuk setiap tingkat variabel independen, "
"disesuaikan untuk semua variabel lain dalam model, dihitung."

msgctxt "MarginalMeans|"
msgid ""
"When this option is selected, the bootstrapped marginal means are "
"calculated. By default, the number of replications is set to 1000. This can "
"be changed into the desired number."
msgstr ""
"Ketika opsi ini dipilih, rerata margin bootstrap dihitung. Secara bawaan, "
"jumlah replikasi diatur ke 1000. Ini dapat diubah menjadi angka teringinkan."

msgctxt "MarginalMeans|"
msgid ""
"By selecting this option, the adjusted means are compared to 0 and the "
"confidence intervals of the adjusted means are calculated."
msgstr ""
"Dengan memilih opsi ini, rerata tersesuai dibandingkan dengan 0 dan interval "
"kepercayaan rerata tersesuai dihitung."

msgctxt "MarginalMeans|"
msgid "When this option is selected, no adjustment will be applied."
msgstr "Ketika opsi ini dipilih, tidak ada penyesuaian akan diterapkan."

msgctxt "MarginalMeans|"
msgid "Bonferroni correction of the confidence intervals."
msgstr "Koreksi Bonferroni interval kepercayaan."

msgctxt "MarginalMeans|"
msgid "Sidak correction of the confidence intervals."
msgstr "Koreksi Sidak interval kepercayaan."

msgctxt "Models|"
msgid ""
"All the independent variables and covariates that can be included in the "
"model."
msgstr ""
"Semua variabel independen dan kovariat yang dapat disertakan dalam model."

msgctxt "Models|"
msgid ""
"The independent variables and covariates included in the model. By default, "
"all the main effects and interaction effects of factor variables, and the "
"main effects of covariates are included in the model."
msgstr ""
"Variabel independen dan kovariat disertakan dalam model. Secara bawaan, "
"semua efek utama dan efek interaksi dari variabel faktor, dan efek utama "
"dari kovariat disertakan dalam model.."

msgctxt "Nonparametrics|"
msgid ""
"The Kruskal-Wallis test is a non-parametric, rank-based one-way ANOVA that "
"can be used to compare two or more groups. This test is appropriate when the "
"normality assumption is violated and/or when outliers are present. To "
"conduct the test, move the independent variables from the left box to the "
"right box."
msgstr ""
"Uji Kruskal-Wallis adalah non-parametris, ANOVA satu arah berbasis peringkat "
"yang dapat digunakan untuk membandingkan dua atau lebih banyak grup. Uji ini "
"tepat ketika asumsi normalitas dilanggar dan/atau ketika outlier ada. Untuk "
"mengonduksi uji, pindahkan variabel independen dari kotak kiri ke kotak "
"kanan."

msgctxt "Nonparametrics|"
msgid ""
"Request effect size estimates for the Kruskal-Wallis test: rank epsilon "
"squared and rank eta squared, including their confidence interval. Based on "
"the effectsize package."
msgstr ""
"Minta estimasi ukuran efek untuk uji Kruskal-Wallis: peringkat epsilon "
"berkuadrat dan peringkat eta berkuadrat, mencakup interval kepercayaannya. "
"Berdasarkan paket ukuran efek."

msgctxt "Nonparametrics|"
msgid ""
"This non-parametric follow-up test is used for pairwise comparisons after "
"performing the Kruskal-Wallis test. The p-values are corrected using the "
"Bonferroni and Holm methods."
msgstr ""
"Uji tindak lanjut non-parametris ini digunakan untuk perbandingan "
"berpasangan setelah melakukan uji Kruskal-Wallis. Nilai-p dikoreksi "
"menggunakan metode Bonferroni dan Holm."

msgctxt "PostHoc|"
msgid ""
"To perform a post hoc test, drag one or more factor names to the right box. "
"Several options are available:"
msgstr ""
"Untuk melakukan uji pos hoc, seret satu atau lebih nama faktor ke kotak "
"benar. Beberapa opsi tersedia:"

msgctxt "PostHoc|"
msgid "Different types of post hoc tests can be selected."
msgstr "Beberapa jenis uji pos hoc dapat dipilih."

msgctxt "PostHoc|"
msgid ""
"Pairwise t-tests are performed. All the corrections can be applied to this "
"method. When Tukey's p-value correction is selected, this is equivalent to "
"Tukey's HSD. This option is selected by default."
msgstr ""
"Uji-t berpasangan dilakukan. Semua koreksi dapat diterapkan ke metode ini. "
"Ketika koreksi nilai-p Tukey dipilih, ini sama dengan HSD Tukey. Opsi ini "
"dipilih secara bawaan."

msgctxt "PostHoc|"
msgid ""
"By selecting this option, the bootstrapped post hoc test is applied. By "
"default, the number of replications is set to 1000. This can be changed into "
"the desired number."
msgstr ""
"Dengan memilih opsi ini, uji pos hoc terbootstrap diterapkan. Secara bawaan, "
"jumlah replikasi diatur ke 1000. Ini dapat diubah menjadi angka teringinkan."

msgctxt "PostHoc|"
msgid ""
"By selecting this option, the effect size (i.e., the magnitude of the "
"observed effect) will be displayed. The used measure for the effect size is "
"Cohen's d. The effect size will only be displayed for the post hoc type "
"Standard."
msgstr ""
"Dengan memilih opsi ini, ukuran efek (yaitu, besar dari efek terobservasi) "
"akan ditampilkan. Pengukuran terguna untuk ukuran efek adalah d Cohen. "
"Ukuran efek akan hanya ditampilkan untuk Standar jenis pos hoc."

msgctxt "PostHoc|"
msgid ""
"Instead of pairwise comparisons for all possible combination of cells in the "
"interaction, list pairwise comparisons conditional on each of the "
"interaction terms. This provides as many tables as there are terms in the "
"interaction effect."
msgstr ""
"Alih-alih perbandingan berpasangan untuk semua kombinasi memungkinkan sel di "
"interaksi, daftar kondisional perbandingan berpasangan pada setiap istilah "
"interaksi. Ini memberikan sebanyak mungkin tabel istilah di efek interaksi."

msgctxt "PostHoc|"
msgid ""
"This method can be used when equal group variances cannot be assumed. The p-"
"values are adjusted using the Tukey method."
msgstr ""
"Metode ini dapat digunakan ketika varians grup sama tidak dapat diasumsikan. "
"Nilai-p disesuaikan menggunakan metode Tukey."

msgctxt "PostHoc|"
msgid ""
"With this method, all levels are compared to the first occurring level in "
"the data. To change which level is used as the reference group, adjust the "
"order of the level labels in the Variable Settings."
msgstr ""
"Dengan metode ini, semua tingkat dibandingkan ke tingkat kejadian pertama di "
"data. Untuk mengubah di mana tingkat digunakan sebagai grup referensi, "
"sesuaikan urutan label tingkat di Pengaturan Variabel."

msgctxt "PostHoc|"
msgid ""
"To correct for multiple comparisons and avoid Type I errors, various methods "
"are available for adjusting the p-value and confidence interval for mean "
"differences. Note: confidence intervals for effect sizes can only be "
"adjusted using the Bonferroni method."
msgstr ""
"Untuk mengoreksi untuk beberapa perbandingan dan mencegah galat Jenis I, "
"berbagai metode tersedia untuk menyesuaikan nilai-p dan interval kepercayaan "
"untuk perbedaan rerata. Catatan: interval kepercayaan untuk ukuran efek "
"dapat hanya disesuaikan menggunakan metode Bonferroni."

msgctxt "PostHoc|"
msgid ""
"Compare all possible pairs of group means. This correction can be used when "
"the groups of the independent variable have an equal sample size and "
"variance. This method is commonly used and is selected by default."
msgstr ""
"Bandingkan semua pasangan mungkin rerata grup. Koreksi ini dapat digunakan "
"ketika grup variabel independen memiliki ukuran sampel dan varians sama. "
"Metode ini sering digunakan dan dipilih secara bawaan."

msgctxt "PostHoc|"
msgid ""
"Adjusting significance levels in a linear regression, to account for "
"multiple comparisons. This method is considered to be quite conservative."
msgstr ""
"Menyesuaikan tingkat signifikan di regresi linear, untuk memperhitungkan "
"beberapa perbandingan. Metode ini dianggap cukup konservatif."

msgctxt "PostHoc|"
msgid ""
"This correction is considered conservative. The risk of Type I error is "
"reduced, however the statistical power decreases as well."
msgstr ""
"Koreksi ini dianggap konservatif. Risiko dari galat Jenis I dikurangi, namun "
"daya statistikal menurun juga."

msgctxt "PostHoc|"
msgid ""
"This method is also called sequential Bonferroni, and considered less "
"conservative than the Bonferroni method."
msgstr ""
"Metode ini juga disebut Bonferroni sekuensial, dan dianggap kurang "
"konservatif dari metode Bonferroni."

msgctxt "PostHoc|"
msgid ""
"This method is considered less conservative than Bonferroni but still "
"maintains statistical power. It is usually used if there is not a big amount "
"of tests to be performed."
msgstr ""
"Metode ini dianggap kurang konservatif dari Bonferroni tetapi masih "
"dipelihara daya statistikal. Itu biasanya digunakan jika tidak ada jumlah "
"besar uji untuk dilakukan."

msgctxt "PostHocDisplay|"
msgid ""
"When this option is selected, the confidence interval for the mean "
"difference is calculated for every post hoc method except Dunn. By default, "
"this is set to 95%, but it can be adjusted to the desired percentage."
msgstr ""
"Ketika opsi ini dipilih, interval kepercayaan untuk perbedaan rerata "
"dihitung untuk setiap mode pos hoc kecuali Dunn. Secara bawaan, ini diatur "
"ke 95%, tetapai itu dapat disesuaikan ke persentase teringinkan."

msgctxt "PostHocDisplay|"
msgid "Add asterisks to the table to indicate 3 levels of significance."
msgstr ""
"Tambahkan tanda bintang ke tabel untuk mengindikasikan 3 tingkat signifikan."

msgctxt "PostHocDisplay|"
msgid ""
"Set up a compact letter display of all pairwise comparisons, based on "
"'multcomp::cld' and emmeans."
msgstr ""
"Siapkan tampilan huruf kompak dari semua perbandingan berpasangan, "
"berdasarkan 'multcomp::cld' dan emrerata."

msgctxt "SimpleMainEffects|"
msgid ""
"The simple main effects represent the effect of one independent variable for "
"each level of the other independent variable, by conducting an ANOVA for "
"each subset of the data as specified by the moderator variables."
msgstr ""
"Efek utama sederhana merepresentasikan efek satu variabel independen untuk "
"setiap tingkat variabel independen lain, dengan mengonduksikan ANOVA untuk "
"setiap subrangkaian data sebagai ditentukan oleh variabel moderator."

msgctxt "SimpleMainEffects|"
msgid ""
"This box contains all the independent variables included in the analysis."
msgstr "Kotak ini berisi semua variabel independen disertakan dalam analisis."

msgctxt "SimpleMainEffects|"
msgid ""
"Select the independent variable to determine the effect of this variable, "
"conditional on the levels of the moderator factor(s)."
msgstr ""
"Pilih variabel independen untuk menentukan efek variabel ini, kondisional "
"pada tingkat faktor moderator."

msgctxt "SimpleMainEffects|"
msgid ""
"Select the independent variable that will represent the different levels."
msgstr "Pilih variabel independen yang merepresentasikan beberapa tingkat."

msgctxt "SimpleMainEffects|"
msgid "Select an optional, additional independent variable."
msgstr "Pilih variabel independen tambahan, opsional."

msgctxt "SumOfSquares|"
msgid ""
" There are different types of the sum of squares. The choice of the type is "
"important when there are multiple factors and when the data are unbalanced. "
"In an unbalanced design, the different levels of the independent variable do "
"not contain an equal number of observations (e.g., one group contains more "
"observations than another group). In this scenario, the sum of squares type "
"can influence the results."
msgstr ""
" Ada jenis berbeda jumlah kuadrat. Pilihan dari jenis penting ketika ada "
"beberapa faktor dan ketika data tidak seimbang. Dalam desain tidak seimbang, "
"tingkat berbeda dari variabel independen tidak berisi angka sama dair "
"observasi (mis., satu grup berisi lebih banyak observasi dari grup lain). "
"Dalam skenario ini, jenis jumlah kuadrat dapat diinfluens hasil."

msgctxt "SumOfSquares|"
msgid ""
"Sequential sum of squares. It is the reduction of error when each factor of "
"the model is added to the factors already included, preserving the order of "
"factors in the model. The results depend on the order in which the factors "
"are added to the model. This is important to consider when the model "
"contains more than one factor."
msgstr ""
"Jumlah sekuensial kuadrat. Itu adalah reduksi galat ketika setiap faktor "
"dari model ditambahkan ke faktor sudah disertakan, melestarikan urutan "
"faktor di model. Hasil tergantung pada urutan yang di mana faktor "
"ditambahkan ke model. Ini penting untuk mempertimbangkan ketika model berisi "
"lebih dari satu faktor."

msgctxt "SumOfSquares|"
msgid ""
"Hierarchical/partially sequential sum of squares. It is the reduction of "
"error when each factor is added to the model that includes all the other "
"factors, except the factors where the added factor is a part of, such as "
"interactions containing that factor. Langsrud (2003) advises to apply this "
"type for an ANOVA with unbalanced data."
msgstr ""
"Jumlah sekuensial hierarkikal/sebagian kuadrat. Itu adalah reduksi galat "
"ketika setiap faktor ditambahkan ke model yang menyertakan semua faktor "
"lain, kecuali faktor di mana faktor tertambah adalah bagian dari, seperti "
"interaksi berisi faktor itu. Langsrud (2003) menyarankan untuk menerapkan "
"jenis ini untuk ANOVA dengan data tidak seimbang."

msgctxt "SumOfSquares|"
msgid ""
"Partial sum of squares. It is the reduction of error when each factor is "
"added to the model that includes all the other factors, including "
"interactions with this factor. This type is often selected, because it takes "
"interactions into account (Langsrud, 2003). This type is selected by default."
msgstr ""
"Jumlah kuadrat parsial. Itu adalah reduksi galat ketika setiap faktor "
"ditambahkan ke model yang menyertakan semua faktor lain, mencakup interaksi "
"dengan faktor ini. Jenis ini sering dipilih, karena itu membutuhkan "
"penghitungan interaksi (Langsrud, 2003). Jenis ini dipilih secara bawaan."

msgctxt "RainCloudPlots|"
msgid "The independent variables included in the analysis."
msgstr "Variabel independen disertakan dalam analisis."

msgctxt "RainCloudPlots|"
msgid ""
"Select the independent variable that should be displayed on the horizontal "
"axis of the plot."
msgstr ""
"Pilih variabel independen yang harus ditampilkan pada sumbu horizontal "
"diagram."

msgctxt "RainCloudPlots|"
msgid ""
"By placing an independent variable in this box, different plots "
"corresponding to the different levels of the independent variable will be "
"displayed."
msgstr ""
"Dengan menempatkan variabel independen di kotak ini, beberapa diagram sesuai "
"dengan beberapa tingkat variabel independen akan ditampilkan."

msgctxt "RainCloudPlots|"
msgid ""
"Changes the orientation of the raincloud difference plot so that the x-axis "
"represents the dependent variable."
msgstr ""
"Mengubah orientasi diagram perbedaan raincloud jadi sumbu-x "
"merepresentasikan variabel dependen."

msgctxt "Manova|"
msgid ""
"MANOVA allows the user to analyze the difference among groups when there are "
"multiple dependent variables"
msgstr ""
"MANOVA mengizinkan pengguna untuk menganalisis perbedaan antar grup ketika "
"ada beberapa variabel dependen"

msgctxt "Manova|"
msgid "Assumptions"
msgstr "Asumsi"

msgctxt "Manova|"
msgid "The dependent variables are normally distributed for every group."
msgstr "Variabel dependen secara normal didistribusikan untuk setiap grup."

msgctxt "Manova|"
msgid ""
"The independent variables are categorical, the dependent variables are "
"continuous."
msgstr "Variabel independen kategorikal, variabel dependen kontinu."

msgctxt "Manova|"
msgid "The population covariance matrices of each group are equal."
msgstr "Matriks kovarians populasi dari setiap grup sama."

msgctxt "Manova|"
msgid "The groups are independent."
msgstr "Grup independen."

msgctxt "Manova|"
msgid "The variable of interest. Also called the outcome variable."
msgstr "Variabel fokus. Juga disebut variabel hasil."

msgctxt "Manova|"
msgid ""
"The variables that are manipulated/define the different groups. These are "
"also called the independent variables."
msgstr ""
"Variabel yang dimanipulasi/tentukan grup berbeda. Ini juga disebut variabel "
"independen."

msgctxt "Manova|"
msgid "Components and model terms"
msgstr "Istilah komponen dan model"

msgctxt "Manova|"
msgid "All the independent variables that can be included in the model."
msgstr "Semua variabel independen yang dapat disertakan dalam model."

msgctxt "Manova|"
msgid ""
"The independent variables included in the model. By default all the main "
"effects and interaction effects of the specified independent variables are "
"included in the model."
msgstr ""
"Variabel independen disertakan dalam model. Secara bawaan semua efek utama "
"dan efek interaksi variabel independen tertentu disertakan dalam model."

msgctxt "Manova|"
msgid "display the intercept term in the MANOVA and ANOVA tables."
msgstr "tampilkan istilah intersep dalam tabel MANOVA dan ANOVA."

msgctxt "Manova|"
msgid ""
"Select the statistical test to be performed for the MANOVA and how the F-"
"ratio is approximated."
msgstr ""
"Pilih uji statistikal untuk dilakukan untuk MANOVA dan bagaimana rasio-F "
"diperkirakan."

msgctxt "Manova|"
msgid ""
"Pillai's trace. Produces a value between 0 and 1. The closer to 1, the more "
"evidence there is of an effect of the independent variable on the dependent "
"variable."
msgstr ""
"Pelacakan Pillai. Memproduksikan nilai antara 0 dan 1. Lebih mendekati 1, "
"lebih banyak bukti bahwa ada efek variabel independen pada variabel dependen."

msgctxt "Manova|"
msgid ""
"Wilks' lambda. This can be interpreted as the proportion of the variance in "
"the outcomes that is not explained by an effect."
msgstr ""
"Lambda Wilk. Ini dapat diinterpretasikan sebagai proporsi varians dalam "
"hasil yang tidak dijelaskan oleh efek."

msgctxt "Manova|"
msgid ""
"Hotelling-Lawley's trace. Measures multivariate separation between group "
"means relative to within group variance. Meaning how well can two groups be "
"distinguished taking all the dependent variables into account."
msgstr ""
"Pelacakan Hotelling-Lawley. Mengukur pemisahan multivariat antara rerata "
"grup dibandingkan dengan varians grup. Artinya seberapa baik dua kelompok "
"dapat dibedakan dengan mempertimbangkan semua variabel."

msgctxt "Manova|"
msgid ""
"Roy's largest root. Measures the largest separation between group means "
"along the most discriminating direction in the multuvariate space."
msgstr ""
"Akar terbesar Roy. Mengukur pemisahan terbesar antara rerata grup "
"berdasarkan arah terdiskriminatif dalam ruang multivariat."

msgctxt "Manova|"
msgid " Box's M-test for homogeneity of covariance matrices."
msgstr " Uji-M Box untuk homogenitas matriks kovarians."

msgctxt "Manova|"
msgid "Generalized Shapiro-Wilk test for multivariate normality."
msgstr "Uji Shapiro-Wilk Terhasilkan untuk normalitas multivariat."

msgctxt "Manova|"
msgid "Outputs individual ANOVA tables per dependent variable."
msgstr "Mengeluarkan tabel ANOVA individu per variabel dependen."

msgctxt "Manova|"
msgid ""
"Shows the maximum ratio of the likelihood of the obtained p value under H1 "
"vs the likelihood of the obtained p value under H0. For example, if the two-"
"sided p-value equals .05, the Vovk-Sellke MPR equals 2.46, indicating that "
"this p-value is at most 2.46 times more likely to occur under H1 than under "
"H0"
msgstr ""
"Menampilkan rasio maksimum dari kemungkinan nilai p terambil di bawah H1 vs "
"nilai p terambil di bawah H0. Contohnya, jika nilai-p dua sisi sama "
"dengan .05, MPR Vovk-Sellke sama dengan 2.46, mengindikasikan bahwa nilai-p "
"ini kemungkinan lebih banyak 2.46 kali lebih besar terjadi di bawah H1 dari "
"di bawah H0"

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasures|"
msgid "Q-Q plot residuals"
msgstr "Residu diagram Q-Q"

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasures|"
msgid ""
"Displays Q-Q plot of the standardized residuals. The confidence band shows "
"the expected range of residuals under normality; points outside the band "
"suggest deviations from normality."
msgstr ""
"Menampilkan diagram Q-Q residu terstandardisasi. Rentang kepercayaan "
"menampilkan rentang terharap residu dalam normalitas; titik di luar rentang "
"menyarankan deviasi dari normalitas."

msgctxt "AnovaRepeatedMeasures|"
msgid "Confidence interval"
msgstr "Interval kepercayaan"

msgctxt "DescriptivesPlots|"
msgid ""
"Display central credible intervals in the plot. By default this is set to "
"95%. This can be changed into the desired percentage."
msgstr ""
"Tampilkan interval kredibel pusat dalam diagram. Secara bawaan ini diatur ke "
"95%. Ini dapat diubah menjadi persentase teringinkan."

msgctxt "AssumptionChecks|"
msgid "Q-Q plot residuals"
msgstr "Residu diagram Q-Q"

msgctxt "AssumptionChecks|"
msgid ""
"Displays Q-Q plot of the standardized residuals. The confidence band shows "
"the expected range of residuals under normality; points outside the band "
"suggest deviations from normality."
msgstr ""
"Menampilkan diagram Q-Q residu terstandardisasi. Rentang kepercayaan "
"menampilkan rentang terharap residu dalam normalitas; titik di luar rentang "
"menyarankan deviasi dari normalitas."

msgctxt "AssumptionChecks|"
msgid "Confidence interval"
msgstr "Interval kepercayaan"

msgctxt "DescriptivePlots|"
msgid ""
"Display error bars in the plot. The error bars can represent either "
"confidence intervals or standard errors."
msgstr ""
"Tampilkan bilah galat dalam diagram. Bilah galat dapat direpresentasikan "
"baik interval kepercayaan atau galat standar."
